column2: SELECT MIN(timestamp) AS first_event_timestamp, MAX(timestamp) AS last_event_timestamp, (MAX(timestamp) - MIN(timestamp)) AS time_elapsed FROM event_log WHERE idcase IN ( SELECT idcase FROM event_log WHERE activity IN ('end trip', 'declaration rejected by employee', 'payment handled') );
column3: select p.idcase, strftime('%s', p.timestamp) - strftime('%s', e.start_time) as 'End trip', strftime('%s', x.timestamp) - strftime('%s', e.start_time) as 'Declaration rejected by employee', strftime('%s', y.timestamp) - strftime('%s', e.start_time) as 'Payment handled' from event_log p inner join (select MIN(timestamp) as start_time, idcase FROM event_log GROUP by idcase) e on e.idcase = p.idcase and p.activity = 'End trip' left join event_log x on x.idcase=e.idcase and x.activity = 'Declaration rejected by employee'  left join event_log y on y.idcase=e.idcase and y.activity = 'Payment handled'

column2: SELECT MIN(timestamp) AS first_event_timestamp, MAX(timestamp) AS last_event_timestamp, (MAX(timestamp) - MIN(timestamp)) AS time_between_events FROM event_log WHERE idcase IN ( SELECT idcase FROM event_log WHERE activity IN ('end trip', 'declaration rejected by employee', 'payment handled') ) GROUP BY idcase;
column3: select p.idcase, strftime('%s', p.timestamp) - strftime('%s', e.start_time) as 'End trip', strftime('%s', x.timestamp) - strftime('%s', e.start_time) as 'Declaration rejected by employee', strftime('%s', y.timestamp) - strftime('%s', e.start_time) as 'Payment handled' from event_log p inner join (select MIN(timestamp) as start_time, idcase FROM event_log GROUP by idcase) e on e.idcase = p.idcase and p.activity = 'End trip' left join event_log x on x.idcase=e.idcase and x.activity = 'Declaration rejected by employee'  left join event_log y on y.idcase=e.idcase and y.activity = 'Payment handled'

column2: SELECT idcase, ( JULIANDAY( ( SELECT timestamp FROM event_log WHERE activity IN ('end trip', 'declaration rejected by employee', 'payment handled') AND idcase = el.idcase ORDER BY timestamp LIMIT 1 ) ) - JULIANDAY(timestamp) ) * 24 * 60 AS time_elapsed_minutes FROM event_log AS el WHERE activity = 'start trip';

column3: select p.idcase, strftime('%s', p.timestamp) - strftime('%s', e.start_time) as 'End trip', strftime('%s', x.timestamp) - strftime('%s', e.start_time) as 'Declaration rejected by employee', strftime('%s', y.timestamp) - strftime('%s', e.start_time) as 'Payment handled' from event_log p inner join (select MIN(timestamp) as start_time, idcase FROM event_log GROUP by idcase) e on e.idcase = p.idcase and p.activity = 'End trip' left join event_log x on x.idcase=e.idcase and x.activity = 'Declaration rejected by employee'  left join event_log y on y.idcase=e.idcase and y.activity = 'Payment handled'

column2: SELECT MIN(timestamp) AS first_intervention, MAX(timestamp) AS last_intervention, resource, cost FROM event_log WHERE activity IN ('Intervention', 'End of trip', 'Employee rejection', 'Payment') GROUP BY resource ORDER BY resource;
column3: select p.idcase, strftime('%s', p.timestamp) - strftime('%s', e.start_time) as 'End trip', strftime('%s', x.timestamp) - strftime('%s', e.start_time) as 'Declaration rejected by employee', strftime('%s', y.timestamp) - strftime('%s', e.start_time) as 'Payment handled' from event_log p inner join (select MIN(timestamp) as start_time, idcase FROM event_log GROUP by idcase) e on e.idcase = p.idcase and p.activity = 'End trip' left join event_log x on x.idcase=e.idcase and x.activity = 'Declaration rejected by employee'  left join event_log y on y.idcase=e.idcase and y.activity = 'Payment handled'

column2: SELECT el1.idcase, el1.activity AS first_activity, el1.timestamp AS first_timestamp, el2.activity AS last_activity, el2.timestamp AS last_timestamp, (el2.timestamp - el1.timestamp) AS time_between_activities FROM event_log AS el1 JOIN event_log AS el2 ON el1.idcase = el2.idcase WHERE el1.activity = 'start trip' AND el2.activity IN ('end trip', 'declaration rejected by employee', 'payment handled') ORDER BY el1.idcase, el1.timestamp;
column3: select p.idcase, strftime('%s', p.timestamp) - strftime('%s', e.start_time) as 'End trip', strftime('%s', x.timestamp) - strftime('%s', e.start_time) as 'Declaration rejected by employee', strftime('%s', y.timestamp) - strftime('%s', e.start_time) as 'Payment handled', f.activity from event_log p inner join (select MIN(timestamp) as start_time, idcase FROM event_log GROUP by idcase) e on e.idcase = p.idcase and p.activity = 'End trip' left join event_log x on x.idcase=e.idcase and x.activity = 'Declaration rejected by employee'  left join event_log y on y.idcase=e.idcase and y.activity = 'Payment handled' inner join (select MAX(timestamp) as end_time, activity, idcase FROM event_log WHERE activity='End trip' or activity= 'Declaration rejected by employee' or activity='Payment handled' GROUP by idcase) f on f.idcase=e.idcase

column2: SELECT idcase, ( SELECT timestamp FROM event_log WHERE activity = 'declaration approved by supervisor' AND idcase = el.idcase ORDER BY timestamp DESC LIMIT 1 ) - ( SELECT timestamp FROM event_log WHERE activity = 'declaration submitted' AND idcase = el.idcase ORDER BY timestamp ASC LIMIT 1 ) AS duration FROM event_log AS el WHERE activity = 'declaration approved by supervisor';
column3: WITH RankedEvents AS (SELECT id, activity, timestamp, LEAD(timestamp) OVER (PARTITION BY idcase ORDER BY timestamp) AS next_timestamp, idcase FROM event_log) SELECT idcase, coalesce((strftime('%s', next_timestamp) - strftime('%s', timestamp)),0) as duration FROM RankedEvents WHERE activity='Declaration approved by supervisor'
